        Product description

        • Is this desk suitable for my height, and what is the height range?

          Yes, the height is adjustable from 28.3" to 46.5", easily accommodating your sit-to-stand needs.

        • Are tools included for assembly? Is assembly complicated?

          Yes, all necessary tools (like Allen wrenches) are included. While the provided tools work, a power screwdriver is recommended to speed up assembly.

        • What should I do if the desk won't move or shows an error code?

          Please check the last section of the instruction manual. It explains common error codes and provides quick troubleshooting and reset steps to solve most minor issues yourself.

          5.0 out of 5 stars Pricy for the sturdiness of the product.
          Reviewed in the United States on February 16, 2024
          Color: BlackSize: 55Verified Purchase
          ##UPDATE after my initial review, a manager for Claiks reached out and provided a solution for my situation with the desk (read below). Claiks went above and beyond in customer care, attentiveness and professionalism. They were understanding and courteous all the way thru while the we worked on the solution for my issuea replacement for my table top. First time doimg business with them and they did not let me down. Thank you.

          ##UPDATE
          Reached out to amazon and let's see what happens. Currently holding for the rep to come back hope i am still connected. Nope, amazon rep did not come back to the phone or called me back but I received an email for feedback. Definitely will provide one.

          I asked the amazon tech to help me with the screw issue and her answer was that i could return it. I did not want to return it but maybe do something about the problematic screw or the front tabletop. Since obviously they place the two screws in the middle nub at the bottom for a reason... stability.

          I also reached out to the Seller for support and asked them the warranty time and support. The seller respond with a message that basically said to send them a video to review the issue so they can investigate. Again the issue is: 1 of 2 screws in the middle nub at the bottom of the front tabletop piece is spinning and wont tighten. When I try to screw it in to hold down the front tabletop.

          They did respond to the warranty question an it is 2 years in case anyone is wondering. Support is not in the U.S.

          ##ORIGINAL REVIEW
          I did a search for desks and found some good ones. This one had higher ratings from the ones I was looking at. First the base seems ok when it comes to sturdiness. The assembly was easy, it took me some time but it was easy to follow (no tooling included, except a small L wrench). Width of the desk also good.

          The quality of the pieces seems good. My only complain is the tabletop is not a single piece but composed of two pieces (front and back). The tabletop pieces are very thin about 1/2 in thickness. It feels like when I rest my forearms to support my hand to type on my computer the desk moves (i can see my monitor shaking - sometimes) and the front most piece of the tabletop gives a feeling like is going to bend in the middle because the base does not have any support in the middle where the tabletop sits.

          Also, since the tabletop is two pieces, you can feel the unevenness where the two pieces meet to create a full tabletop. One last thing on the tabletop, if you buy the black tabletop expect to see your finger and hand marks/smears on it.

          One of the screws in the middle nub (small piece of metal with two holes for two screws that connects the front piece of the tabletop) at the bottom of the tabletop keeps on spinning meaning it is not holding down the front most tabletop piece.

          I feel for the price I can buy something better. There are others desks like this for $30 and $40 dollars less that may have the same specs as this one or better. They are other ones i feel are better for $20 to $400 more. You decide.

          Overall don't expect an office quality desk for $200. You may want to look somewhere else if that is what you looking for. This desk also does not include any warranty on the page... amazon sends you to the seller just to see the warranty. Other desk are cover by a 3 year warranty.

          My one star is for support both amazon and the seller, wasted time, sturdiness of the desk, price, thickness and the pain to return an item because no-one knows how to fix the issue.
